bilingual.source: A few years later, one of my sisters got married to a clerk.
bilingual.target: 几年后，我的一个姐妹嫁给了一名职员。

bilingual.source: She married into a rich and powerful family.
She married into the peerage and became a countess.
bilingual.target: 她嫁入了贵族身份，成为了一名伯爵夫人。
她嫁给了一位黎巴嫩人。
她嫁给了一个有钱的商人。

bilingual.source: She married a kind homme last year.
bilingual.target: 她去年嫁给了一个善良的男人。
她嫁给了一个小康的商人。

yingyinNormal.en: There's the man I married.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这才是我嫁的好男人

yingyinNormal.en: Because she married an idiot.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为她嫁给了一个白痴。

yingyinNormal.en: That's why I married him. Yeah, we're sophisticated adults.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以我才嫁给他了。我们是富有经验的成年人。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, do you see, do you see what you're keeping me married too?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你看你让我嫁的是什么人？

yingyinNormal.en: Miss Lucas is married and settled. And one of my own daughters too.
yingyinNormal.zh: 卢卡斯小姐结婚后了，有了归宿了，我自己的一个女儿也出了嫁。

yingyinNormal.en: Monica's right. We're talking about getting married here. Okay? She can't just rush into this.
yingyinNormal.zh: 莫妮卡说得对，这可是婚姻大事，她不能说嫁就嫁。

yingyinNormal.en: Maybe I just wanted to believe you'd do the right thing. Because the man I married would have.
yingyinNormal.zh: 也许我只是想相信你会做正确的事，因为我嫁的男人会。

yingyinNormal.en: Honey, you know. I once also almost married somebody that I didn't love. Do you remember Barry?
yingyinNormal.zh: 坐下，宝贝，你知道吗？我也曾差一点嫁个我不爱的人。

yingyinNormal.en: So I moved to DC, and met the good guy, and I got married at the nearly decrepit age of 24.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我于是搬到哥伦比亚特区，在"老迈"的24岁找个男人嫁了。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《Facebook COO谢丽尔·桑德伯格哈佛演讲》

yingyinNormal.en: If you wanted a husband who proved his manhood to you that way, you should've stayed back in Dallas with your mother and married the prom king.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你要是需要你丈夫那样对你展现阳刚之气，还不如跟你妈待在达拉斯，嫁个舞会国王。

yingyinNormal.en: Do you ever feel that way about Howard? Oh, that's not really a fair comparison. I'm basically married to a sexy Buzz Lightyear.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你对霍华德有过这种感觉吗？拿我男人跟你男人比不太公平啊，我嫁的可是性感版的巴斯光年。

yingyinNormal.en: Seems marvellous to me you leave service, go into government. Now you're married to a prominent man. 20th century story. I agree.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真是不可思议，你辞掉仆人工作，进入政府，现在嫁了一个好男人，真是二十世纪的故事。是啊。

yingyinNormal.en: The next time, she married for the sake of her daughters. But that man, too, was taken from her. And she was doomed to look every day upon his beloved child.
yingyinNormal.zh: 后来一次，她为了她女儿的利益嫁了人。但是那个男人也被死神带走了。而她注定要每天看着他心爱的孩子。

yingyinNormal.en: Daisy loved me when she married me, and she loves me now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 黛西嫁给我时就爱着我，现在也是。

yingyinNormal.en: Did you guys know Penny married Zack three years ago? What?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们知道Penny三年前嫁给了Zack吗？啥？

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, hey, you guys. And this is Loretta. She's married to Paul, who's a werewolf.
yingyinNormal.zh: 嘿，伙计们，这是洛雷塔，她嫁给了保罗，他是个狼人。

yingyinNormal.en: All right. Madonna was married to this Ridgemont high alum. Oh, my god! Sean Penn!
yingyinNormal.zh: 好，麦当娜嫁给了哪位"开放的美国学府"子弟？我的天，肖恩·潘。

yingyinNormal.en: And the destination? I don't care. Whatever's the cheapest. I'm so lucky I married you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 目的地是？随便，最便宜的吧，我嫁给你真是太走运了哈。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, I met a really cute girl at work. She's married to a guy in one of our drug trials.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我工作时遇到了个可爱的女孩儿，她嫁给了我们那儿一位药品临床试验者。

yingyinNormal.en: Once upon a time, there was a beautiful young girl who married for love. And she had two loving daughters.
yingyinNormal.zh: 从前，有一个美丽的年轻女孩嫁给了自己心爱之人。她有两个可爱的女儿。

examination_example.sentence: The most challenging moments in life are getting <highlight>married</highlight>, starting a family and ultimately retiring.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人生中最具挑战性的时刻是结婚、组建家庭和最终退休。

examination_example.sentence: Today's farm laborers, while still predominantly born in Mexico, are more likely to be settled rather than migrating and more likely to be <highlight>married</highlight> than single.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 今天的农场工人虽然仍然主要出生在墨西哥，但更有可能选择定居而不是移民，并且更有可能结婚而不是单身。

examination_example.sentence: Across generational lines, Americans continue to prize many of the same traditional milestones of a successful life, including getting <highlight>married</highlight> and having children.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 跨越世代，美国人继续珍视一个成功人的一生中所要具有的一些不变的传统里程碑，其中包括结婚和生子。

examination_example.sentence: In this case, the Mothering Justice activist happened to be <highlight>married</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在这种情况下，“母亲正义”活动家也是已婚人士。

examination_example.sentence: In 1970, when I was 20, I got <highlight>married</highlight> and moved out of my parents' modest place into a housing project.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 1970年，我20岁的时候，结婚了，从父母那简陋的地方搬进了一间住房。

examination_example.sentence: I did get <highlight>married</highlight>, but had more than two children.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我确实结婚了，但有不止两个孩子。

sense_info_list.en: If you are married, you have a husband or wife.
